:: Ask [en] {"position":"2100,250","size":"100,100"}
I edged closer, my voice trembling. "Hello? Please... do you know how we can leave this place?"

The man let out a dry, mocking chuckle. His eyes swept over us with pure scorn. "The park closes at ten-thirty sharp," he said. "Didn't you bother to read the signs? You're lucky I'm not on the enforcement squad. If I were, you wouldn't even be 'present' anymore."

He laughed again, a cold, hollow sound. "The chances of getting out now are slim to none. Once you're stuck here, the park rarely lets go."

His words plunged Samuel and me into a fresh wave of panic. Watching our faces drain of color, the staff member seemed to relish our fear.

"But," he continued with a glint of malicious glee in his eyes, "I do know a place that might grant your little wish. Follow me."

{[[Next->Page 18]]
(display:"Styles")}
