:: Do not look back, run for your life immediately [en] {"position":"2475,250","size":"100,100"}
I lunged into the staff passage, my lungs screaming for air. Just as Mabel's mechanical thuds were right behind me, a door cracked open and I was yanked into a dim room.

"Are you okay?" a girl asked, her voice hushed.

"I'm Astor," the boy next to her said. "And I'm Clara," she added.

I struggled to catch my breath. "I'm... thank you. Thank you for saving me."

Samuel, collapsed in the corner, was trembling violently. "Was that... was that Mabel?" he stammered. "She’s... she’s horrible... I’ve lost my friends. We got separated in the chaos... I don't know where they are..."

"I'm so sorry," Clara whispered, placing a hand on his shoulder.

"It’s okay," I said, though my eyes remained fixed on the door. "But do you have any idea what’s happening? Why are we even here? This whole thing... it’s driving me crazy!"

The weight of losing everyone was finally breaking Samuel.

Astor looked at us with a grim expression. "We don't know why we were pulled into this world either," he said, reaching into his bag. "But... we just discovered this."

[[Next -> Page 21]]
(display:"Styles")


:: Don't ask [en] {"position":"2100,375","size":"100,100"}
We maintained a cautious distance, our eyes never leaving him as we slowly backed away.

"If there's anything you'd like to ask, I'm right here to help," he said, his voice smooth—perhaps too smooth.

Samuel and I exchanged a quick, uncertain glance. We were both torn; every instinct screamed at us to run, yet the dark blue uniform he wore was a symbol of safety according to the rules.

"Did you end up trapped here by mistake?" the staff member asked, tilting his head.

We gave a small, hesitant nod.

"I can lead you to a safe place," he offered, gesturing toward the darker part of the forest.

We were still drowning in doubt, but the rules were the only anchor we had in this nightmare. The ones in dark blue are trustworthy, I reminded myself. With no better options, we stepped into the shadows behind him.

{[[Next->Page 18]]
(display:"Styles")}
