:: DrifterStory [en] {"position":"2775,800","size":"100,100"}
We moved like shadows across the open pavement, our breaths held tight. We were so close to the entrance of Colorful World, but then, it happened.

The air behind us grew cold, thick with the smell of ozone and wet fur. Then came the sound—a high-pitched, mechanical whine layered beneath a woman's hollow weeping.

Mabel.

She was faster than before. Her heavy, rhythmic thuds vibrated through the ground, closing the gap with terrifying speed. With no time to run for the open passage, we were driven like cattle into a dark corner, forced to seek shelter in the only place left.

