:: Stand your ground, too terrified to move [en] {"position":"1600,200","size":"100,100"}
I stood rooted to the spot, not daring to flinch. The rule was clear: Do not leave without instruction. I clung to that sentence like a lifeline, quickly shoving my phone into my pocket. My entire body shook as I stared into the contorted, hideous face of the creature before me.

The staff member tilted its head, its voice a sickening, dry rasp.

"So obedient," it hissed. "And yet... you are still too late."

Before I could even gasp, its jagged, inhuman claw lunged forward. It didn't just stab me; it skewered my chest. A dull, cold shock radiated from the wound, followed by a searing heat that consumed my lungs.

I looked down, watching my own blood drench the very rules I had tried so hard to follow. Darkness began to cloud my vision, and as my heart gave its final, frantic thud, I realized the cruelest truth of this park:

In here, the rules weren't meant to save you. They were only meant to keep you still long enough for the slaughter.
(display:"Styles")


:: Start [en] {"position":"100,300","size":"100,100"}
Recently, a newly opened theme park has seen an astonishing influx of visitors, as if everyone were irresistibly drawn to it. 

Particularly captivating is the |highlight>[circus performance] at the |imp>["Dreamland Circus,"] which has just recently opened. 

Word has it that some guests are so enamored with this circus that they visit three to four times a week, which seems quite exaggerated. 

As a content creator, I couldn't resist riding the wave of this popularity to attract viewers, so I booked tickets to the circus. Due to the overwhelming number of attendees, the only remaining options for entry were at night; all other times had already sold out. I had hoped to spend a leisurely day there, but I felt rather helpless.

[[Next->page 1]]
(display:"Styles")


